<title>Postcards from the Sequoias</title>
<META name="description" content="Russell D. Hoffman's Visits the Sequoias and comes back with pictures">
<META name="keywords" content=" Sequoias sequoia National Park Kings
Canyon National Park World's largest living things Sequoiadendrum
giganteum or giant sequoia High Sierra San Joaquin Valley Fresno
California Grant Grove Giant Forest redwoods 
">
</head>
<body>
<hr>
<h1> Pictures from the Sequoias </h1>
Sequoias are related to 
<a href="/misc/stories/redwoods/redwoods.htm">California Redwoods</a>
but are generally a litte shorter and a little wider at the base.  
These pictures were taken by Russell D. Hoffman in 1996 in Kings Canyon 
National Park and Sequoia National Forest, California.  Camera: Mamiya 
m645J with a Mamiya-Sekor 80mm 1:2.8 lens or a Mamiya-Sekor 150mm 
1:3.5 telephoto lens.  
<a href="seqlarge.htm">Click here to download all large versions at
once--about 1.8 megabytes (9 images).</a> 
<hr>
<a href="foursequ.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=138 SRC="fourseq4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<a href="busequoi.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=135 HEIGHT=200 SRC="busequo4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<a href="deadlog2.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=137 SRC="deadlog4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<p><br>
<a href="deadupr.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=132 HEIGHT=200 SRC="deadupr4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<a href="moistseq.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=139 SRC="moistse4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<a href="onebigse.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=132 HEIGHT=200 SRC="onebigs4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<p><br>
<a href="threemst.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=136 SRC="threems4.gif" ALT=""></a>
<a href="trunkseq.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=10 WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=200 SRC="trunkse4.gif" ALT=""></a>
