<title> Petition to Stop CASSINI, NASA's Plutonium Probe </title>
<META name="description" content="Petition to Stop Cassini, NASA's Plutonium Probe">
<META name="keywords" content="space debris junk satellite NASA astronauts 
shuttle space station orbital orbit man-made missile plutonium Russian 
probe nuclear waste Chernobyl environmentalism environment nature 
radiation atomic cancer Mars '96 probe Proton Booster Baikonur 
Global Surveyor Pathfinder Cassini RTG nukes Cassini Florida Kennedy
Space Center Cape Canaveral Cosmodrome Kazakstan Red Planet Mars Canada
uranium radioactivity radioactive isotopes Roentgen rads thermonuclear war">
</head>
<body>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=184 SRC="stopc200.gif" ALT="">
<a href="/cassini/cassini.htm"><h1>CANCEL CASSINI</h1></a>
<h2>No Plutonium in Space!</h2>  
<hr>
We, the undersigned, call upon NASA and our elected officials to
suspend plans to launch the Cassini space probe to Saturn as long as
any plutonium is scheduled to be on board.  Presently, the project
calls for 72.3 pounds of plutonium 238 to generate on-board
electricity.  The risk of an accident at launch or during its
"slingshot fly-by" above the Earth is not worth the gamble.  We urge
the use of alternative on-board power sources such as solar energy
and long-life fuel cells for all future space missions. 
<p>
