<title>Tutorial About GENI, Part 1 of 4</title>
</header>
<body>
<a name="top"> </a>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/nm_ma256.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/nm_ma256.gif" ALT="Global Energy Network International"></a>
<hr>
<!MOVE '3.56' TO VERSION_NUMBER>
<p>
GENI is a U.S. tax exempt 501(c)(3) corporation committed to improving the quality of life for everyone without damage to the planet.
<p>
Copyright (c) 1994-1997 by:
<br>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/geniname.gif"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/geniname.gif" ALT="Global Energy Network International"></a>
<br>
P.O. Box 81565
<br>
San Diego CA 92138 USA
<hr>
<h3>A Solution to Global Problems</h3>
<hr>
<h3> What the Experts are Saying </h3> 
<p>
"A global energy network makes enormous sense if we are to meet global energy needs with a minimal impact on the world's environment"
Al Gore, as Senator, Tennessee
<p>
"Electrical interconnections between regions -- even between continents -- can and must be tackled now"
Walter Hickel, as Governor of Alaska
<p>
"The extensive international cooperation necessary would mean alternative expenditures to armaments"
Yevgeny Velikhov as VP of Russian Academy of Sciences
<p>
"The most thoughtful and scientific solution to the world's problems I've seen"
Ron Williams, Director of R&D, General Motors
<p>
<h3>A Global Challenge</h3>
<b>Inventor, scientist, and mathematician R. Buckminster Fuller asked the question:</b>
<p>
<b>"How do we make the world work for 100% of humanity in the shortest possible time through spontaneous cooperation without ecological damage or disadvantage to anyone?"</b>
<hr>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/buckymcg.gif"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/buckymcg.gif" ALT="Photo of R. Buckminster Fuller"></a>
R. Buckminster Fuller
<br>
1895-1983
<br>
A bibliography is provided at the end of this presentation.
<br>
<hr>
<h3>Fuller Projection Dymaxion Globe</h3>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/dymamcg1.gif"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/dymamcg1.gif" ALT="Dymaxion Globe"></a>
<br>
To answer this question, Buckminster Fuller invented the Dymaxion (tm) globe and map.
<p>
The Dymaxion Globe has many advantages:
<br>
Unfolded, it has very little distortion and no breaks in the continental contours.
<p>
The word Dymaxion (tm) and the Dymaxion Map design are trademarks of The Buckminster Fuller Institute.
<p>
The Dymaxion Map is copyrighted by The Buckminster Fuller Institute 1938, 1967, 1980 and 1992. All Rights Reserved.
<p>
<hr>
<br>
<h3>Fuller Projection Dymaxion Globe</h3>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/dymaunfl.gif"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/dymaunfl.gif" ALT="Dymaxion Globe Unfolded"></a>
<p>
The Dymaxion map shows that all the continents are connected, or separated by relatively short distances.
<p>
This "one-world island in a one-world ocean" helps us visualize global resources, population and distribution patterns which characterize the complex trends and critical needs of today's world.
<p>
<hr>
<h3>Energy is Vital to Our Quality of Life</h3>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/coffeema.gif"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/coffeema.gif" ALT="Coffee Maker"></a>
<a href="/pics/geni/genimcga/sewingma.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM HSPACE=20 SRC="/pics/geni/genimcga/sewingma.gif" ALT="Sewing Machine"></a>
<p>
Electricity is the most versatile form of energy, powering nearly every modern convenience:
<p>
Refrigeration, lighting, telephones, sewage systems -- even the computer you're using right now.
<p>
