<h1>STOP CASSINI</h1></a>
<h1>ACTION PLAN</h1>  
<h2>These are things YOU can do to help stop the October 1997
launch of over 72 pounds of plutonium into space on the Cassini
mission:</h2>
<p>
<DL> 
   <DT> <b>1)</b> Get signatures on the <a href="petition.htm">Stop Cassini Petition</a>
and send them to 
<a href="http://www.afn.org/~fcpj/index.htm">Florida Coalition for Peace & Justice</a>.
   <DT> <b>2)</b> Show the award-winning "Nukes in Space" video in your
community.  (It can be ordered from the 
<a href="http://www.afn.org/~fcpj/index.htm">Florida Coalition for Peace & Justice</a>
 for $19.95.)
   <DT> <b>3)</b> Start a local chapter of the Global Network Against
Weapons and Nuclear Power in Space in your community to oppose the
Cassini launch.  Just let us know and we will send you materials.
   <DT> <b>4)</b> Invite Global Network spokespersons to speak in your
community.  Call the FCPJ at (352) 468-3295 to set up an event.
   <DT> <b>5)</b> Write letters to the editor of your local paper about
Cassini.
   <DT> <b>6)</b> Organize a letter-writing campaign to your Congressperson
about the plutonium on Cassini.
   <DT> <b>7)</b> Send delegations to visit or hold a vigil at your
Congressperson's office.
   <DT> <b>8)</b> Send a donation to the FCPJ.  This is a grass-roots campaign funded
entirely by donations. 
   <DT> <b>9)</b> Don't think you can't make a difference.  You and people
just like you are the only thing that can.
<DL>
<h3>Main Talking Points:</h3>
</DL>
   <DT> <b>1)</b> The nuclear industry views space as a new market.
   <DT> <b>2)</b> As more and more plutonium is launched in space,
eventually an accident could happen... technology <i>does</i> fail!
   <DT> <b>3)</b> Plutonium is the most toxic substance known, and the
deadliest way to spread it is through the atmosphere--<i>just</i>
like Cassini will do if it fails!
   <DT> <b>4)</b> The European Space Agency has stated they could provide
solar power for the Cassini deep space mission.
   <DT> <b>5)</b> Space missions like Cassini are ice-breakers; they get
everyone used to the idea of nuclear power in space so that people
will later accept the use of full-blown nuclear reactors in space for
Star Wars and it's deadly "High-Tech" Weapons Platforms.
</DL>
