<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: The Chamber: Growth and Development</title>
</head>

<body background="./graphics/goldmrbl.jpg">
<h3>Growth and Development</h3>
<hr>

<p>Moore County's thriving economy is the result of a successful balance of tourism, retirement, health care, agriculture and manufacturing. Situated halfway between New York and Florida and halfway between the Blue Ridge Mountains and the Carolina coastline, our location has significantly contributed to the strong economy and tremendous growth over the last decade.

<p>Tourism in Moore County has for the past century been one of our major strengths.  Each year the county attracts thousands of visitors from all corners of the world.  The Convention and Visitors Bureau for the Village of Pinehurst, Southern Pines, Aberdeen Area reports an economic impact of travel in Moore County for 1993 of $157.5 million. On average a North Carolina county generates $1,200 per capita in travel and tourism sales, but Moore County generates $2,833 per capita - nearly two-and-a-half times the state average.

<p>The area travel industry employs over 4,500 people in the county and represents a collective payroll of $42.8 million.  Each year the growth rates of visitors to our county have increased by 20%.  And our future looks even brighter.

<p>Major golf events in our area have brought people to us in vast numbers. In 1994, Pinehurst  Resort and Country Club was the host of the US Senior Open, in 1995 the LPGA Women's Championship was played at Pinewild Country Club.  This year, Southern Pines' Pine Needles Resort is home to the US Women's Open golf tournament.  And to cap off the decade, in 1999 the US Open will be held here at Pinehurst. Golf has been a catalyst for tourism in Moore County, but there is plenty else that brings `em here.  We have other attractions and events throughout the county each year that bring thousands of visitors to our doors.  

<p>Our villages and towns with their unparalleled hospitality and warmth combine historical charm with unique shopping experiences.  Regionally the area has become recognized as a major shopping area. Two of the nation's mass retailers have built new stores within the last three years.  New specialty shops have been opening their doors to visitors and locals alike. Dining in our county is a myriad of multicultural tastes.  An exciting variety of restaurants exists in the area now and is ever increasing.  This not only translates into revenue for our residents, but contributes to our extremely high quality of life.

<p>As a result of our pleasant community, temperate climate, and convenient location, Moore County has become an attractive place for retirement.Retiree relocation has spurred the growth of adult community housing developments. Independent living communities are available for those who no longer wish to maintain a home and property.  The county's retirees are the backbone of the area's volunteer efforts.  Their commitment to the continued improvement in the quality of life is evident from their involvement in everything from serving patient needs at Moore Regional Hospital to tutoring children in the Moore County Schools.

<p>Moore County is proud to be the home of Moore Regional Hospital, a regional referral center that has experienced phenomenal growth in the last decade. Under the hospital's leadership, health care has become a major sector of the county's economy.  The hospital is one of the county's largest employers.  Growth in the services it offers has attracted new physicians and added the availability of new medical specialties to the region.  Home health services, Hospice services and skilled nursing care facilities also strengthen the health care sector of Moore County's economy.

<p>Agriculture serves as important part of Moore County's economic mix.  Our farmers compete globally with their products, and contribute over $135 million annually to the local economy.  Tobacco and poultry represent two of the largest segments of the local agricultural market.  Produce abounds as well in the Sandhills.  Peach orchards, strawberry farms, pumpkin patches and a Farmer's Market offer a variety of fresh produce throughout the year.

<p>A variety of light manufacturing industries make their home in Moore County.  Textiles are the mainstay of the county's manufacturing base. Machine tool fabrication and furniture manufacturing represent most of the remaining manufacturing mix. Four of the area's largest employers are manufacturers. Manufacturing employs roughly 25% of the area's labor force.

<p>Moore County's economy is thriving. The tourism industry is not only successful, but is a catalyst for growth in other industries. Our economic base is diverse and job opportunities abound. Moore County continues to benefit from a strong economy that translates into a high quality of life for our residents.  

