                 entertainment, food and fun.  Hours:  Monday-Friday: 5
                 PM to Midnight; Saturday-Sunday: 1 PM to Midnight. 
                 Ft. Bragg Fairgrounds.  For more information call
                 (910) 396-3919.

  12 - 13        ALL HARLEY DRAG RACING ASSOCIATION FINALS.  Rockingham
                 Dragway, Rockingham.  For more information call
                 (910) 582-3400.

  14 - 18        MATCH PLAY CHAMPIONSHIP, WOODLAKE COUNTRY CLUB, VASS.  
                 On the 16th there will be a Men's N/S Challenge with a
                 1 PM shotgun start.  For more information call
                 (919)245-4686 or (910) 245-4031.

  15             NC SYMPHONY POP'S CONCERT, "FIT FOR A KING".  Hours: 
                 8 PM.  Pinecrest High School Robert E. Lee Auditorium.
                 For more information call (910) 692-4356.

  17             NC/SC MUNICIPAL COUNCIL GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Mid Pines
                 Inn & Golf Club.  For more information call
                 (910) 692-2114.

  17             NC MOTOR SPEEDWAY GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Country Club of
                 Whispering Pines.  For more information call
                 (910) 949-2311.

  18 - 20        INAUGURAL MID PINES SENIOR INVITATIONAL GOLF
                 TOURNAMENT.  Mid Pines Inn & Golf Club.  For more
                 information call (910) 692-2114.

  19             19TH ANNUAL HOLLY ARTS AND CRAFTS FESTIVAL.  Pinehurst
                 Business Guild.  More than 150 exhibitors, crafts,
                 food, entertainment and more.  Hours:  10 AM-4 PM. 
                 Village of Pinehurst.  For more information call
                 (910) 295-5700.

  19 - 20        AC DELCO 200/400.  NC Motor Speedway.  Start your
                 engines please and head for "The Rock"; Winston Cup
                 Series NASCAR Races.  All the big name drivers will be
                 there!  Rockingham.  For more information call
                 (910) 582-2861.

  20 - 22        CAROLINA'S SENIOR OPEN GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Mid Pines Inn
                 & Golf Club.  For more information call (910) 692-2114.

  22             "TURKEY - WHERE EAST MEETS WEST."  Kiwanis of the
                 Pines and Sandhills Community College Travelogue.  
                 Travel with Phil Slayton as he takes you from
                 Istanbul in the west, Mt. Ararat in the east, the
                 Mediterranean in the south to the Black Sea in the
                 north.  Hours:  8 PM.  Performing Arts Center,
                 Southern Pines.  For more information call
                 (910) 692-4356.

  22 - 25        FIRETHORN/CPGA MATCH PLAY PRO-AM CHAMPIONSHIP GOLF
                 TOURNAMENT.  Woodlake Country Club, Vass.  For more
                 information call (910) 245-4686.

  22 - 25        PGA TOUR QUALIFYING - FIRST STAGE GOLF TOURNAMENT.  
                 Magnolia Course, Pinewild Country Club, Pinehurst. 
                 For more information call (910) 295-5145.

  24             N.C. COAL INSTITUTE GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Mid Pines Inn &
                 Golf Club.  For more information call (910) 692-2114.

  24 - 27        SANDHILLS LITTLE THEATRE PRESENTS "THE CURIOUS
                 SAVAGE".  A comedy by John Patrick.  Heart-stirring
                 and comedic tale of an elderly woman's determination
                 to live her life with the virtues of kindness and
                 affection.  Tickets are $10 Thurs. & Sun., $12 Fri. &
                 Sat.; 50% student discount .  Hours: 
                 Thursday-Saturday 8 PM, Sunday Matinee 2:30 PM.  Owens
                 Auditorium, Sandhills Community College.  For more
                 information call (910) 692-3799.

  25 - 26        NHRA SOUTHEAST SEARS/CRAFTSMAN E.T. FINALS.  
                 Rockingham Dragway, Rockingham.  For more information
                 call (910) 582-3400.

  25 - 27        NCRTPA STATE CHAMPIONSHIP TENNIS TOURNAMENT.  (North
                 Carolina Recreational Tennis Players Association.)
                 3.0, 4.0, 5.0.  Hours:  8 AM.  Pinehurst Tennis Club. 
                 For more information call (910) 295-8556 or
                 (910) 295-6811.

  26 - 27        BOO AT THE ZOO.  Annual daytime alternative to
                 Halloween trick-or-treating with games, prizes and
                 entertainment at the North American Plaza.  NC
                 Zoological Park, Asheboro.  For more information call
                 (800)488-0444.

  31             HALLOWEEN HAUNT.  Recreation Department.  Halloween
                 games, refreshments, hayride, haunted house.  Hours: 
                 5-7 PM.  Train House, Campbell House grounds, Southern
                 Pines.  For more information call (910) 692-2463.

  October 31 -   SANDHILLS LITTLE THEATRE PRESENTS "THE CURIOUS
  November 2     SAVAGE".  A comedy by John Patrick.  Heart-stirring
                 and comedic tale of an elderly woman's determination
                 to live her life with the virtues of kindness and
                 affection. Tickets are $10 Thur.; $12 Fri. & Sat.;
                 Students 50% discount.  Hours:  Thursday-Saturday 8
                 PM.  Owens Auditorium, Sandhills Community College. 
                 For more information call (910) 692-3799.

