<HEAD><TITLE>Sandhills.Net: December Events</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center><H2>December 1996</h2></center>
<HR>
<pre>

  December 1 -   LAWN BOWLING.  Visitors welcome to participate in lawn
  December 31    bowling at the weekly club bowling days, Mondays,
                 Wednesdays and Saturdays.  Pinehurst Flag Circle
                 Green, Pinehurst Resort & Country Club.  For more
                 information call (910) 295-6689.

  2 - 5          IZOD CLUB CAROLINA'S PRO-PRO CHAMPIONSHIP GOLF
                 TOURNAMENT.  Mid Pines Inn & Golf Club; Pine Needles
                 Lodge & Golf Club; Pinehurst Plantation.  Hours:  8
                 AM.  For more information call (910) 692-2114 or
                 (910) 695-3193.

  4              FT. BRAGG CHRISTMAS TREE LIGHTING.  Hours: 4:30 PM;
                 entertainment, tree lighting after dark; refreshments
                 served.  Community Center, Knox & Randolph Roads.  For
                 more information call (910) 396-3919 or (910) 396-6319.

  5              "CAROLS AT WEYMOUTH",  a special "open house".  The
                 community is invited to see the downstairs of Boyd
                 House beautifully decorated.  Traditional music
                 programs.  Hours:  5:30 PM & 7:00 PM.  Weymouth
                 Center, 555 Connecticut Avenue, Southern Pines.  For
                 more information call (910) 692-6261.

  6              EXHIBIT OPENING.  Campbell House Feature Gallery
                 artists: LDDK Pottery (Seagrove Area potter); Jan
                 Chenoweth, acrylics.  Campbell House, Connecticut
                 Avenue, Southern Pines.  For more information call
                 (910) 692-4356.

  6              PINEHURST VILLAGE TREE LIGHTING.  The village fills
                 with Christmas spirit as festivities start mid
                 afternoon with refreshments, entertainment and
                 hayrides; visitors and locals come for this annual
                 event.  The lighting of the majestic tree is 6:30 PM.  
                 For more information call (910) 295-8505.

  6 - 8          WEYMOUTH CENTER OPEN HOUSE  The local garden clubs
                 decorate Weymouth Center in live greens along with
                 their Christmas decorations.  Admission fee $5.00.  
                 Hours:  Friday 10 AM-5 PM; Saturday 10 AM-5 PM. 
                 Weymouth Center, 555 E. Connecticut Avenue, Southern
                 Pines.  For more information call (910) 692-6261.

  6 - 8          CAROLINA AMATEUR FIELD TRIALS.  Hours:  8 AM to late
                 afternoon.  Sandhills Wildlife Area, Hoffman, NC.  For
                 more information call (704)596-6816.

  6 - 21         CHRISTMAS IN THE VILLAGE OF PINEHURST.  Every Friday
                 and Saturday until Christmas, step back in time during
                 holiday season in historic Pinehurst, with lights &
                 luminaries and village shopkeepers in period costume. 
                 Enjoy special music/entertainment, carriage rides.  
                 Refreshments served from tea cart Friday &
                 Saturday, noon-2 PM.  For more information call
                 (910) 295-6508.

  6 - 25         PINEHURST TWELVE DAYS OF CHRISTMAS.  Pinehurst Resort
                 & Country Club.  December 6th-8th, 13th-15th,
                 20th-24th and brunch on the 25th. Christmas Music from
                 Medieval to Dickens to Christmas Carols. For more
                 information and reservations call: (910) 295-8434.   

  7              9TH ANNUAL MOORE COUNTY PARKS & RECREATION JR. CLASSIC
                 GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Max. age 18.  Mid Pines Inn & Golf
                 Club.  For more information call (910) 692-2114.

  7              PARADE AND CHRISTMAS TREE LIGHTING, SOUTHERN PINES.  
                 Join in the festivities leading into the holiday
                 season.  Hours:  3 PM parade begins, tree lighting
                 follows.  Downtown Southern Pines.  For more
                 information call (910) 692-8161.

  7              (TENTATIVE DATE.)  19TH ANNUAL EPISCOPAL DAY SCHOOL
                 CANDLELIGHT TOUR.  Tour local homes, all decorated in
                 Christmas fashion; entertainment, bake sale, Santa,
                 Christmas carols for young & old. Tour originates at
                 Episcopal Day School, Southern Pines.  Hours:  1-6 PM.
                 For ticket information call (910) 692-3492.

  7              SEVEN LAKES CHRISTMAS SHOWCASE TOUR AND LUNCHEON.  
                 Sponsored by Women's Auxiliary. Starts at Seven
                 Lakes Country Club, 10 AM; luncheon held at North Club
                 House. Limited number of tickets go on sale
                 mid-November.  For more information call (910) 673-7804.

  7 - 8          MOORE COUNTY CHORAL SOCIETY CHRISTMAS CONCERT.  Hours:
                 12/7-8 PM; 12/8-4 PM. Tickets are available at the
                 door.  Owens Auditorium, Sandhills Community College,
                 Pinehurst.  For more information call (910) 692-6481 or
                 (910) 692-6185.

  7 - 8          CHRISTMAS OPEN HOUSE.  Decorations & refreshments. 
                 Hours: 1-4 PM; Bryant House: Saturday and Sunday only,
                 1-4 PM.  For more information call (910) 692-2051 or
                 (910) 691-7811.

  8              MALCOLM BLUE FARM CHRISTMAS OPEN HOUSE.  1825
                 farmhouse is decorated with greenery.  The Junior
                 Historians and friends play and sing Christmas carols.
                 Refreshments are served.  Hours:  12-5 PM.  Malcolm
                 Blue Farm, Aberdeen.  For more information call
                 (910) 944-7558.

  8              CHRISTMAS LIGHTING OF CAMERON.  Walking tour and
                 lighting of candles, gathering for singing of carols
                 and visit three historic churches.  Hours:  5:30 -
                 7:30 PM.  Meet at Greenwood Inn, Cameron.  For more
                 information call Isabel Thomas at (910) 245-7042.

  8              CHRISTMAS OPEN HOUSE VILLAGE OF PINEHURST.  A holiday
                 mood continues in the Village of Pinehurst with
                 costumed shopkeepers and strolling entertainers,
                 noon-4 PM.  (Note: some shops open 10 AM.)
                 Refreshments served from cart, noon-2 PM.  For more
                 information call (910) 295-6508.

  8              CHRISTMAS CANDLELIGHTING AND OPEN HOUSE.  The
                 Historical House in the Horseshoe, north of Carthage. 
                 Hours: 1-8 PM. Free admission.  For more information
                 call (910) 947-2051.

  11 - 15        ATLANTIC COAST SHOOTING DOG CHAMPIONSHIP.  Hours:  8
                 AM to late afternoon.  Sandhills Wildlife Area,
                 Hoffman, NC.  For more information call (704)596-6816.

  11 - 15        CHRISTMAS OPEN HOUSE  at the historic Shaw House,
                 Britt/Sanders Cabin and Garner House in Southern
                 Pines, by the Moore County Historical Association. 
                 Native greenery, 19th-century decorations &
                 refreshments.  Hours:  1-4 PM.  For more information
                 call (910) 692-2051.

  15             CAROL SING JUBILATTE.  Pinehurst Resort & Country
                 Club.  For more information call (910) 295-6811.

  15             ANNUAL CHRISTMAS CONCERT.  Features college band,
                 choir and orchestra; free.  Hours:  2 PM.  Owens
                 Auditorium, Sandhills Community College.  For more
                 information call (910) 695-3829 or (910) 692-6185.

  20 - 23        REGION 3, ALL AGE CHAMPIONSHIP EVENT FIELD TRIALS.  
                 Hours:  8 AM to late afternoon.  Sandhills Wildlife
                 Area, Hoffman, NC.  For more information call
                 (704)596-6816.

  21             CHRISTMAS HORSE CARRIAGE DRIVE.  View beautifully
                 groomed horses and ponies put to a variety of antique
                 carriages with drivers and horses all dressed up for
                 Christmas.  Hours:  1:30 - 2:30 PM.  Downtown Southern
                 Pines.  For more information call Mary Grey at
                 (910) 692-2449.

  26 - 29        DONALD ROSS JR. CHAMPIONSHIP GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Boys
                 only, max. age 17, Pinehurst Resort & Country Club.  
                 For more information call (910) 295-8140 or
                 (910) 295-6811.

  27 - 28        JUNIOR CHRISTMAS CLASSIC GOLF TOURNAMENT.  Age range
                 10-21.  Woodlake Country Club, Vass.  For more
                 information call (800)334-1126 or (910) 245-4686.

  December 31 -  RING IN THE NEW YEAR PARTY IN THE PINES,  with
  January 1      entertainment: Sound Express. To be held in the Grand
                 Ballroom, Pinehurst Resort & CC.  For ticket
                 information call (910) 295-8415.   

  December 31 -  NEW YEAR CELEBRATIONS.  Check with area inns/resorts
  January 1      to celebrate ringing in 1997.   

