<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: The Chamber: Child Care and After School Care</title>
</head>

<body background="./graphics/goldmrbl.jpg">
<h3>Child Care and After School Care</h3>
<hr>

<p>As increasing numbers of families with small children move into Moore County, the need for quality child care has grown.  We offer several different options for parents. Licensed, free-standing centers accept infants from six weeks of age until pre-school. They offer educational programs as part of their curriculum. Legal child care homes are another option for parents. Several pre-schools operate excellent programs as well.

<p>As after school care for children is a necessity for working parents, Moore County has created after school programs that are available at nearly all of the county's public and private elementary schools.

<p>The Moore County Parks and Recreation Department operates a licensed day-care camp, with locations in Carthage and Pinehurst, during the summer.

<p>A list of all the licensed child care programs in Moore County is available through Child Care Connections, a private, non-profit child care resource and referral agency, located in Southern Pines. This private, non-profit organization coordinates child care services in the community with parental needs, and promotes public awareness of quality child care. The agency works closely with parents to help them find the right child care situation.

<hr>
<center>
