<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: The Chamber: Recreation</title>
</head>

<body background="./graphics/goldmrbl.jpg">
<h3>Recreation</h3>

<ul>
<li>Golf
<p>For over eighty-five years the Sandhils have been the home of world famous golf! With 38 courses and more under construction our county is known as the "Golf Capital of the World!"  Nestled between quaint villages and towns, our spectacular courses are expertly designed and groomed to excite all levels of golfers. Tradition hangs over these courses like a silent cloud. It is difficult not to be awestruck by their history.  You can literally walk in the footsteps of legends....Palmer, Nicolas, Hogan, Snead...and many many more.

<p>Our courses are truly championship. We have had the honor to host such tournaments as the 1991 and 1992 PGA Tour Championships and the 1994 Senior Open at the Pinehurst Resort and Country Club. In 1995 Pinewild was the proud home of the LPGA  Championship. This year we are proud to welcome the 1996 US Women's Open to our Pine Needles resort in Southern Pines. This is an especially exciting event in that we will help raise funds for breast cancer research.  And to cap off the decade we will again be honored as we host the 1999 US Open at Pinehurst.

<p>Remember these courses are now yours!  Come tee off often.
<br><br>

<li>Equestrian 
<p>Moore County has the distinct honor of being known as "horse country." Horseback riding through the tranquility of our majestic countrysides is a renewing pleasure.  A day  of harness racing or polo at the Pinehurst Track is a fun-filled family event. The famous Stoneybrook Steeplechase is a major event popular for over 45 years. Each April thousands gather from up and down the eastern seaboard to celebrate in the form of a grand finale the end of the hunting season and the beginning of spring.

<p>Whether you like to ride on a peaceful trail through the woods, compete in world-class events, or share the day with friends and family at the track...you'll have plenty of opportunities to enjoy the world of equestrian sports in Moore County.
<br><br> 

<li>Bicycling
<p>International cycling teams have long regarded Moore County as a top training ground. There are a variety of mapped courses through our villages and towns. Annually the exciting Tour de Moore challenges bikers on a 100-mile road race around the perimeter of the county culminating with a grand finish in Southern Pines.

<p>If competitive riding is not your cup of tea, a day of leisurely cycling throughout our lovely towns and villages is always a pleasure.
<br><br>

<li>Tennis
<p>Tennis in the Sandhills is always smashing! There are many public courts available for residents to enjoy as well as private exclusive clubs.  Lessons are available as well, so bring your racquet!
<br><br>

<li>And more...
<p>We literally have something for everyone.  There is so much that the entire story can not be told in one spot. A great source of information for activities is one of our area's parks and recreation departments. There are three in our county:  the Moore County Parks and Recreation Department, the Southern Pines Department of Recreation and the Aberdeen Parks and Recreation Department.  

<p>These organizations sponsor events for children, adults and seniors. There are team activities, such as baseball, basketball and softball, holiday events such as Easter egg hunts, the Jingle Bell Festival, and Lake Eerie at Halloween.  Lessons, excursions, and much more is open to the residents of Moore.
<br><br>

<li>Fitness Center
<p>The Moore Regional Health and Fitness Center, a part of Moore Regional Hospital, offers membership opportunities to all county residents. Opened in February 1995, the beautiful complex houses an assortment of recreational facilities.  These include racquetball courts, basketball and volleyball courts, swimming pool, whirlpool, sauna, and excercise rooms. A full schedule of fitness classes, covering strength training, aerobics, Dietcise, a weight loss and excercise program, and a comprehensive aquatics program.
<br><br>

<li>Gardens
<p>Botanical Gardens are a special treat. The Sandhills Horticultural Gardens, located on the campus of Sandhills Community College, covers over 23 acres and is open to the public every day of the year from dawn to sunset.

<p>The gardens are composed of a variety of plants and differences in landscape design. Visitors can stroll through the impressive Rose Garden, Conifer Garden, formal English Garden, and the largest accessible Holly garden on the East Coast.  There is much more, so be sure to go often.
<br><br>

<li>Parks, outdoor activities
<p>If you enjoy picnicking, boating and fishing, you will find Moore County has several places for you to enjoy the outdoors. Parks abound in the area. Cannon Memorial Park, in Pinehurst, and Downtown Park, in Southern Pines, are a children's paradise with their imaginative playgrounds. Reservoir Park, located at the site of the old Southern Pines reservoir, has a picnicking shelter and tables beside a beautiful lake where canoeing and fishing are permitted.The Whitehall Trails System in Southern Pines has fitness trails to enjoy and nature walks are available throught the <a href="http://ils.unc.edu/parkproject/wewo.html">Weymouth Center</a>.
</ul> 				
		
<p>Recreation is a major part of the lives of Moore County's active community. We have unique opportunities for sports of all kind. There is truly something for everyone.  Be your game golf, tennis, lawnbowing, croquet or one of our other numerous options, you can find it here. There is so much to do, and so many new things to try. 

<hr>
<center>
<A HREF="./index.html"><img align=bottom border=0 src="./graphics/bluebal2.gif" alt=" * "> The Sandhills Home Pages: Main</A>
</center>

</body>
</html>
