<head>
<title>The Sandhills.Net Home Pages: History</title>
</head>

<body background="./graphics/goldmrbl.jpg">
<h3>History</h3>
<hr>
<p>Pinehurst, the historic center of modern day Moore County, celebrated its Centennial during 1995. Founder James Walker Tufts established Pinehurst, a complete resort village with an elegant inn and turn of the century luxuries during the late 1800's. At that time, the region was known as an area where one could receive treatment for certain health ailments.

<p>People began to seek refuge from the northern blizzards by flocking to the resort towns that provided the prescribed fresh air and mineral water. Meanwhile the small towns that dotted the county became incorporated and self functioning. Donald Ross, legendary golf course designer responsible for the famous No. 2 Course, and many other favorites in the area, introduced golf to the area--and the Sandhills area has made history ever since.

<p>Moore County, however has roots that trace back as early as the beginning of the sixth century. Archaeological findings indicate that Indians of the Siouan family inhabited this area until about 400 years ago. A well-used Indian trail which crosses the county is thought to have been beaten out by buffaloes on their annual migrations from the Piedmont to the coastal marshes. This trail, which later came to be known as the Yadkin Road, played an important role in early settlement of Moore County.

<p>The earliest European settlers came to the region about 1739. During the ensuing years, additional settlers, largely English, Ulster Scots, and Germans moved into the area, traveling down the "Great Wagon Road" from Pennsylvania or up the Cape Fear River Valley from Wilmington. Most settled on the Deep River in northern Moore County. By the mid-1750's, the area was sparsely, but evenly, settled.

<p>The next twenty years saw a large influx of settlers, particularly Highland Scots. These Highlanders settled in southeast Sandhills, an area bypassed by earlier settlers due to the poorness of the soil. The industrious Scots made the best of what they had and soon established the manufacture of naval stores as a major industry of the vast forest of longleaf pines. Moore County, named after Alfred Moore of Brunswick, officially became a county in 1783.

<p>As the region's growth began to accelerate, the effects of the Civil War proved particularly hard on Sandhills citizens. But in the 1870's with the arrival of the Raleigh and Augusta Railroad, little towns began to evolve, resort business flourished, and the region quickly became a commercial center.

<p>Today, Moore County natives and newcomers alike benefit from a lifestyle rich in history and tradition. Welcome to the Sandhills and enjoy!

<hr>
<center>
<A HREF="./index.html"><img align=bottom border=0 src="./graphics/bluebal2.gif" alt=" * "> The Sandhills Home Pages: Main</A>
</center>

