<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: The Chamber: Neighborhoods and Housing</title>
</head>
<body background="./graphics/goldmrbl.jpg">
<h3>Neighborhoods and Housing</h3>
<hr>
<p>Life in Moore County is like living in a big small town. While we offer many of the services and amenities of much larger areas, you still experience the joys of a close-knit community in our towns and developments.

<p>The county's towns each have their own special history and personality. Robbins, located in northern Moore County, was originally named Hemp, and has long been a thriving textile center. Carthage, the county seat, was once home to the Tyson and Jones Buggy Company. Pinehurst and Southern Pines initially developed as resort communities which attracted individuals looking for a place to relax and restore their health. Aberdeen was settled by Scottish Presbyterians. Within each of these communities, you will find a variety of housing from classic older homes in the heart of town to modern, suburban style subdivisions.

<p>Moore County's growth has prompted the development of newer communities offering the convenience of 24-hour security and resort-like recreational activities.  There are several country club developments as well in our area. If you are interested in communities designed to accommodate the needs of persons 50 years of age and older, you will find several neighborhood options.

<p>Moore County enjoys the diversity of being a small cosmopolitan area with the beauty and tranquility of a rural community. The southern end of the county between Southern Pines and Vass is divided into lovely mini-farms and horse country. Throughout Moore County working farms and homes on large tracts of land create beautiful, scenic surroundings. One of the area's realtors can help you find exactly what you are looking for. Our tremendous variety in neighborhoods offers something to suit everyone's needs and interests!

