<HEAD><TITLE>Sandhills.Net: Search Hints</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY background="./graphics/pearl.jpg" bgcolor=#FFFFFF>

<h2>Search Hints</h2>
<hr><p>

<font size=+1>Use the form below to search through the pages of the <b>Sandhills Electronic Village</b>. For searches covering the entire World Wide Web, explore the sources on our <a href="lib-link.html">Library Links</a> page.</font><p>

<h3>Enter Text</h3>

<blockquote>This search tool can be tailored to fit your specifications.  For a simple search involving only one term--such as <i>golf</i>--just type the word into the box labeled "Text to Search For" and click the [Search!] button.  This will produce a list of all the pages on our site which contain the word <i>golf</i>.  Each title in the list is a hot-link to the page itself, which you can reach by clicking on the title.</blockquote><p>

<h3>Boolean  (AND / OR)</h3>

<blockquote>You can also enter two or more words to search for, and specify how the words are related by using the Boolean terms (sometimes called "logical operators") AND and OR.  If you want to see a list of just those pages on which <b>both</b> <i>golf</i> <b>and</b> <i>retirement</i> appear, enter both words in the "Text to Search For" box and select AND.  On the other hand, if you want a list of all the pages on which <b>either</b> <i>golf</i> <b>or</b> <i>retirement</i> appears, select OR.</blockquote><p>

<h3>Case (Insensitive / Sensitive)</h3>

<blockquote>Does it matter whether the terms in question use capital or 
lower-case letters? If the Case box reads "Insensitive" and you search for 
<i>Golf</i>, the list will include pages which contain <i>golf</i> as well as those 
which contain <i>Golf</i>, <i>GOLF</i> . . . or even <i>gOLf</i>.  On the other hand, 
if you select "Sensitive" and search for <i>Golf</i>, the search will produce only 
those pages containing that word with the first letter capitalized and all the rest lower-case.</blockquote>
<p>

<font size=+1>Click the [Search!] button to perform the search, or the [Reset] button to 
change your search options.</font><p>

