-->
<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: The Chamber: Assisted Living and Senior Services</title>
</head>

<body background="./graphics/goldmrbl.jpg">
<h3>Assisted Living and Senior Services</h3>

<p>Moore County, an area with a significant senior population, takes pride in the ammenities available to meet their needs.  We work to ensure that they lead active and fulfilling lives for all of their years. We have several types of facilities and organizations to address every level of assistance that may be necessary.

<p>The Moore County Department of of Aging is committed to maintaining the independence and dignity of older adults in their own home and through various community-based services. The Department works with Moore County Transportation Services and volunteers to transport older adults to medical appointments, to shopping and errands, and to employment. Home Care Services can be secured through the Department. Interested seniors can participate in daily activities planned at each of  four Nutrition Sites throughout Moore County. The program provides recreational and educational offerings, fellowship, a hot lunch meal, exercise and arts and crafts.

<p>Together with Meals-on-Wheels, which services the Southern Pines- Aberdeen-Pine Bluff area, the Department delivers a hot lunch meal to homebound senior citizens throughout the county. The Department offers free consultation for individuals interested in assistance in evaluating and acquiring supplemental Medicare insurance. It sponsors the Senior Games In The Pines, the Annual Senior Citizens Handicraft and Hobby Fair, and has compiled an Elder Care Directory of Information for Senior Citizens in Moore County.

<p>Five intermediate care facilities provide personal and residential care, along with regular medical, rehabilitative and social services, as necessary. Moore County has four nursing homes that serve 24-hour health care needs that do not require the intensive care of a hospital.

<p>Whatever the level of assistance needed for our seniors, we have a wide variety of choices from which to choose. Here in Moore County our seniors are considered a special part of our society. We treat them with the respect and dignity they deserve and strive to make sure each of their years is golden.

<hr>
