<head>  
<title>Sandhills.Net: Education: Post-secondary Education</title>  
</head>  
  
<body BACKGROUND="./graphics/ivrmrbl2.gif">  
<!-- start body stuff here -->  
<h2><font size=+3 color="0000ff">P</font>ost-secondary <font size=+3 color="0000ff">E</font>ducation</h2>  
<hr>  
<p><font size=+3>M</font>oore County is the proud home of <a href="http://www.sandhills.cc.nc.us/Sandhills/">Sandhills Community College</a>, the first comprehensive community college in the State of North Carolina, and a premier jewel in the state's comm

unity college system. The school offers one-year vocational and diploma programs, and two-year associates degrees, including a college transfer program. The Division of Continuing Education serves over 10,000 residents county-wide with a range of programs

 covering everything from painting to on-site help for business and industry.  
  
<p><font size=+3>I</font>ndividuals interested in earning a four-year 
college degree will find several opportunities close to home. 
<a href="http://www.sapc.edu/"> St. Andrews Presbyterian College</a>, 
based in Laurinburg, North Carolina, operates a program on the Sandhills 
Community College campus for those who have already earned an associate's 
degree, or the equivalent. Louisburg College, located in Louisburg, and 
Pembroke State University, located in Pembroke, offer a range of degree 
programs. <a href="http://www.campbell.edu/">Campbell 
University</a>, in Buies Creek, offers an impressive 
undergraduate curriculum and professional education in pharmacy, law 
and business. Notably, Moore County is just an hour's drive away from 
North Carolina's other renowned state and private universities: 
<a href="http://www.unc.edu/">University of North Carolina</a>, 
<a href="http://www.ncsu.edu/">North Carolina State University</a>, 
<a href="http://www.duke.edu/">Duke University</a>, and 
<a href="http://www.wfu.edu/www-data/start.html">Wake Forest 
University</a>.
<p>
Educational opportunities abound in Moore County, and our commitment 
to excellence in education is just one more reason why we are notably 
proud of our quality of life.
<p>
<hr>  
For more information about this site, or to suggest additional materials, 
please <A HREF="mailto:info@sandhills.net"><b>send us e-mail.</b></A><P>
