Anyone who resides in one of the five counties of the Sandhills  
Regional Library System may apply for a library card at no cost.  
The System includes Anson, Hoke, Montgomery, Moore, and  
Richmond Counties.<p> 
 
<hr> 
<P> 
<DL> 
 
<A NAME="sppl"><B>Southern Pines Public Library</B></A><P> 
<dt>Municipal Library for the Town of Southern Pines<BR> 
Lynn Thompson, Director<P> 
<dd>170 West Connecticut Avenue<BR> 
Southern Pines, NC<br> 
(910) 692-8235<p> 
 
Hours:<BR> 
10:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m., Monday - Thursday<BR> 
10:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m., Friday - Saturday<BR> 
2:00 p.m. - 5:00 p.m., Sunday<BR> 
<P> 
</DL> 
Residents of Southern Pines qualify for a library card at no 
charge. Adult non-residents pay $35 annually and juvenile 
non-residents pay $10 annually for borrowing cards. 
<P> 
 
<HR> 
<DL> 
<A NAME="given"><B>Given Memorial Library</B><p> 
