<HR> 
<P> 
<a name="schools"><B>Media Centers of Moore County Schools</B> 
<P> 
<DL> 
</dl> 
<P><hr><P> 
<A NAME="hcic"><B>Health Care Information Center</b><P> 
<DL> 
<DT>FirstHealth of the Carolinas<br>
<DT>Moore Regional Hospital<p>

<DD>P. O. Box 3000<BR> 
Page Road<BR> 
Pinehurst, NC 28374<P> 
 
Location: 2nd Floor, Administration Conference Center<BR> 
Phone: (910) 215-1588 
Hours: 8:30 a.m. - 3:00 p.m., Monday - Friday<P> 
 
</dl>

The Healthcare Information Center is pleased to offer health related information services to the public, and is currently expanding its Community Health collection. This collection includes a number of reference books written in lay terms, as well as CD-ROM resources and videos, which
may be used in the Information Center.<p>

The provision of health related information to the public is provided as a community educational service. It is not a substitute for professional medical advice from a doctor or other health-care professional. Our services are meant to clarify and augment information already obtained from a medical doctor or other health-care professional, and/or to help the recipient formulate better questions to ask a doctor or other health-care professional about medical conditions.<p>

<HR><P> 

 
Send us questions and comments <a href="mailto:info@sandhills.net"><b>via e-mail</b>.</a> 
