<head>  
<title>Sandhills.Net: Education: County/Public Schools</title>  
</head>  
  
<body BACKGROUND="./graphics/ivrmrbl2.gif">  
<!-- start body stuff here -->  
<h2><font size=+3 color="0000ff">C</font>ounty/<font size=+3 color="0000ff">P</font>ublic <font size=+3 color="0000ff">S</font>chools</h2>  
<hr>  
<p><font size=+3>T</font>he county has nineteen public schools: eleven
elementary schools, four   
middle schools and three high schools. The schools are currently  
implementing a program of reduced class size in kindergarten through third  
grade. Plans have recently been approved for the building of two new middle   
schools. These facilities will serve the Vass/Cameron and WestEnd/Pinehurst   
areas of the county.  
  
<p><font size=+3>T</font>he public schools benefit from the strength of the school/business   
partnerships they form with local companies.  These companies donate   
equipment to the schools such as microscopes for science classes and file   
cabinets for office needs, as well as other amenities, such as benches and   
shrubbery to spruce up the school grounds. Company employees volunteer their   
time to help children during the school day.  
  
<p><font size=+3>M</font>oore County Schools Tech Prep program is a partnership formed between the schools and <a href="http://www.sandhills.cc.nc.us/Sandhills/"> Sandhills Community College</a>. Designed to help vocational students, the program encourage
s continuation in a two year degree program after the prescribed high school courses. The program benefits students who are not interested in a four-year college degree, but who want to strengthen their job skills before entering the labor force. <p> 
 
<hr>  
 For more information about this site, or to suggest additional materials, 
please <A HREF="mailto:info@sandhills.net"><b>send us e-mail.</b></A><P>
<center> 
<img align=bottom border=0 src="./graphics/bluebal2.gif" alt="*"> 
<A HREF="./index.html"><b> The Sandhills Home Pages: Main</b></A> 
</center> 
 

