<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: Health: Home Health & Hospice</title>
</head>

<body BACKGROUND="./graphics/m0oe9ihe.gif">
<!-- start body stuff here -->
<h2>Home Health & Hospice</h2>
<p>Did you know thousands of Sandhills residents each year receive regular 
visits from licensed Home Health professionals and assistants?

<p>Home Health Agencies and Home Care organizations deliver a wide variety 
of medical, therapeutic, counseling, and assisted living services to area 
residents each day in the privacy and comfort of the patients home.  
From detailed procedures prescribed by physicians to assisting with 
household chores, certified Home Health professionals and support staff 
offer patients a cost-effective alternative to long-term institutional 
care.

<p>Hospice Programs throughout the Sandhills Area also strive to work within 
the home but with a mission of providing care and counseling for 
terminally patients and their families.  With comprehensive and 
compassionate care, Hospice relieves the pain, fear and loneliness of 
patients and their loved ones, thereby enabling them to prepare 
emotionally and spiritually for the end of life.  Patients and their 
families are assisted with this preparation through personalized service 
and a caring support system of professional staff and volunteers.

<h5>Home Health & Hospice Providers:</h5>
<ul>
<li>  Apira Health Care
<li>  Central Carolina Hospital Home Care Store
<li>  Interim
<li>  Paradigm
<li>  Sandhills Hospice
<li>  St. Joseph of the Pines, Inc., PO Box 1179, Pinehurst, NC 28374-1179, (910) 295-3920
<li>  see phonebook listings
</ul>

