<title>Sandhills.Net: SandLink</title><head>

<body background="./graphics/gr_mrbl2.gif">

<h3>What is SandLink?</h3>

SandLink is a committee of the Sandhills Area Chamber of Commerce, located in Southern Pines, North Carolina. Its members currently include representatives of several not-for-profit community  organizations: the Southern Pines Public Library,  County of Moore,  First Health of the Carolinas (Moore Regional Hospital), St. Joseph  of the Pines, Sandhills Community College, Moore County Public Schools,  and the Sandhills Area Convention and Visitors Bureau.
<hr>
<h3>Mission Statement</h3>

SandLink was established to develop a structure to electronically link Moore County's private sectors and public sectors for the purpose of providing a central access network which will promote the internal and external benefits and opportunities of the Sandhills.
<hr>
<h3>History</h3>

In December of 1994, the Sandhills Area Chamber of Commerce convened a Telecommunications and Information Systems Task Force to explore the area's present and future needs in terms of electronic information systems. Membership included a broad representation of local organizations, agencies, and businesses, as well as private citizens of the area.
<p>

At that time, public access to the Internet was available only through long-distance telephone connections to a commercial online service. By the summer of 1995, two Internet service providers had established points-of-presence in Moore County, and SandLink--a subset of the Telecommunications Task Force--was formed to oversee the development of a community-based information infrastructure.
<p>

Development of a site on the World Wide Web continued through the fall and winter of 1995. The site was conceived as an electronic village--a service for area residents, with links to local points of information, commerce, and leisure, as well as to the vast resources of the larger Internet. It would serve also as a source of information for those outside the community interested in learning more about the educational, commercial, governmental and recreational features of the Sandhills.
<hr>
<h3>Today and Tomorrow</h3>

Sandhills.Net came on-line in June of 1996.  Member agencies of SandLink helped to develop the site's primary subdivisions-- Education, Visitor Information, Government, Health, Libraries, and The Chamber. The site will continue to evolve in response to further collaboration among all sectors of the community. For more information about becoming a presence on the Sandhills.Net Web site, get in touch with us:
<p>
<hr>
Sandhills Area Chamber of Commerce<br>
1480 Highway 15-501<br>
Post Office Box 458<br>
Southern Pines, North Carolina 28387<br>
Phone: (910) 692-3926<br>
Fax: (910) 692-0619<br>
<A HREF="mailto:sacc@ac.net">E-Mail: sacc@ac.net</A>

<center>
<img align=bottom border=0 src="./graphics/bluebal2.gif" alt="*"> <A HREF="./index.html"><b> The Sandhills Home Pages: Main</b></A>
</center>


