<head>  
<title>Sandhills.Net: Education: Private Schools</title>  
</head>  
  
<body BACKGROUND="./graphics/ivrmrbl2.gif">  
<!-- start body stuff here -->  
<h2><font size=+3 color="0000ff">P</font>rivate <font size=+3 color="0000ff">S</font>chools</h2>  
<hr>  
<p><font size=+3>O</font>ptions exist for private education in Moore County. 
The O'Neal School,  located in Southern Pines, is an independent college 
preparatory institution. The school has three divisions, offering classes from   
pre-kindergarten through grade 12. O'Neal provides a traditional curriculum   
beginning in pre-kindergarten that includes foreign language, computer, art,   
music and physical education. Advanced Placement courses are offered in the   
upper grades. A learning development program is designed for students with  
learning disabilities.  
  
<p><font size=+3>T</font>he Episcopal Day School. also in Southern Pines, 
is an independent school affiliated with the National Association Of Episcopal 
Schools. The school serves children ages three through fourth grade. The 
school's components include programs in academics, fine arts, physical 
education, library, computer, spiritual studies and special resources.  
  
<p><font size=+3>B</font>oth the O'Neal School and Episcopal Day School are accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools.  
 <p> 
 
<hr>  
 For more information about this site, or to suggest additional materials, 
please <A HREF="mailto:info@sandhills.net"><b>send us e-mail.</b></A><P>
