<head>
<title>Sandhills.Net: Health: Alternative Heath Care</title>
</head>

<body BACKGROUND="./graphics/m0oe9ihe.gif">
<!-- start body stuff here -->
<center><h2>Alternative Health Care</h2></center>

<p>Did you know Alternative Health Care encompasses numerous non-medical 
disciplines from nutritional cooking to yoga?

<p>Alternative Health Care includes all disciplines intended to supplement, 
enhance or take the place of traditional health and medical services 
offered by the established medical community.  In many instances, 
alternative health care provides non-traditional instruction and guidance 
for living healthier, happier lives, often through programs designed to 
increase self-awareness, reduce stress, and offer unconventional outlets 
for stress and creative energies.

<h4>WHITEHALL HEALTH EDUCATION CENTER</h4>
<p>The mission of Whitehall Health Education Center -- a nonprofit educational 
institution in Southern Pines -- is to meet the needs of the community with 
preventive health education through programs and activities involving body, 
mind, emotions and spirit in a homelike and peaceful environment using both 
volunteers and professionals.  Whitehall Center offers health related 
seminars, workshops, classes, lectures, and access to a free library of 
preventive health education information.

<p>Classes provided at Whitehall Center have included exercise and yoga, 
stress management, art, nutritional cooking, and massage therapy.  In 
addition to meeting rooms, Whitehall Center boasts a two-mile walking trail 
that winds through the Centers 150-acres.  Future plans call for an 
outdoor amphitheater, soccer classes, and programs for youth enhancement 
and stress management.

<h5>Alternative Health Care Providers:</h5>
<ul>
<li>  The Hara Foundation (Yoga Instruction), 130 N. Ashe Street, Southern Pines, NC  28387, (910) 692-0995
<li>  Whitehall Health Education Center, PO Box 1221, Southern Pines, NC 28388, (910) 692-6691
</ul>

