<body>
<h2 align=center>Policy Statements Adopted by the AFL-CIO Executive 
Council</h2>
<h3 align=center>December 16, 1996</h3>
<hr size=4 width=80%>
<ul>
<li><a href="srawberr.htm">STRAWBERRY WORKERS MARCH - APRIL 13, 1997</a></li>
<li><a href="security.htm">BLOCK GRANTING ECONOMIC SECURITY PROGRAMS</a></li>
<li><a href="railind.htm">STOP THE RAIL INDUSTRY RAID ON WORKERS_ PENSIONS</a></li>
<li><a href="jobswith.htm">JOBS WITH JUSTICE COALITION</a></li>
<li><a href="bywater.htm">VICE PRESIDENT WILLIAM BYWATER</a><br>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 align=left><a name="aug96">August 7, 1996</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="aug96/csanna.html">Support for Anna Veterans' Home Workers</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csappeal.html">Appeals and Protests Arising from State and Local Cent</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csarticle.html">Article XX Protection for Independent Unions</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csbell.html">Opposition to Bell Atlantic-Nynex Buyout</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csburning.html">Burning of Religious Institutions</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csenglish.html">English as the Official Language of Government Act</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csfoul.html">Foulball Campaing</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csimplem.html">Implementing Article XX of the AFL-CIO Constitution</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csprinc.html">Principles Regarding the Social Security System</a> </li>
<li><a href="aug96/csstate.html">State Central Body Affiliation Fee Fund Disbursement</a> </li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="may96">May 8-9, 1996</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><dl>
</dl>
<p><a href="may96/byctchi.html"><strong>Boycott Chinese-Made Goods</strong></a><strong> </strong></p>
<dl>
<dd>Despite increased international attention and pressure, the Chinese government has 
steadfastly refused to end the ongoing and serious violations of human and trade union 
rights in China.</dd>
</dl>
</li>
<li><a href="may96/acog.html">1996 Olympic Games</a> </li>
<li><a href="may96/sexhar.html">Sexual Harrassment</a> </li>
<li><a href="may96/turner.html">In Memory of Vice President J.C. Turner</a> </li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="feb96">February 1996</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><dl>
</dl>
<p><a href="feb96/ecinvolve.html"><strong>Informing and Involving Union Members in Legislative Debates</strong></a><strong> </strong></p>
<dl>
<dd>After the 1994 election, the federation and many unions went back to the rank and file 
membership -- through meetings, polls, focus groups and other forms of inquiry -- to 
reexamine the connections working people make between their concerns as workers 
and family members and their participation in elections.</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
</dl>
</li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecraise.html">America Needs A Raise</a> <dl>
<dd>America Needs a Raise, Town Hall Meetings to be held between March 15 and May 
31</dd>
</dl>
</li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecreclaim.html">Reclaim America</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecspecial.html">Special Convention</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecguide.html">AFL-CIO Organization Fund Guidelines for Assistance and Support</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecorg.html">Building Power for Workers By Organizing</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecfed.html">The Federal Reserve</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecrugmark.html">RUGMARK Campaign</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecnigeria.html">Nigeria</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ectrade.html">International Trade</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/eelectric.html">Stability of the Electric Utility Industry </a></li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecnireland.html">Northern Ireland</a> </li>
<li><a href="feb96/ecschool.html">School Vouchers</a> </li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="sep95">September 1995</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><dl>
</dl>
<p><a href="sep95/labormvmt.html"><strong>Full Participation in the Labor Movement</strong></a><strong> </strong></p>
<dl>
<dd>In keeping with the instructions of the 1993 AFL-CIO Convention, the AFL-CIO 
established a Full Participation Committee to examine ways in which the labor 
movement might achieve full participation and integration of its diverse membership 
into leadership positions at every level of organization...</dd>
</dl>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="aug95">August 1995</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><dl>
</dl>
<p><a href="affirmat.htm"><strong>Affirmative Action</strong></a><strong> </strong></p>
<dl>
<dd>In the last year, affirmative action has come under ferocious attack. It has been 
undermined and its scope has been limited by a series of court decisions....</dd>
</dl>
</li>
<li><a href="osha.htm">The Assault on Worker Safety and Health</a> </li>
<li><a href="staley.htm">A.E. Staley Mfg. Co. and UPIU Local 7837</a> </li>
<li><a href="wu.htm">Harry Wu </a></li>
<li><a href="transp.htm">A New Tack in the Campaign to Get Rid of American Workers</a> </li>
<li><a href="bieber.htm">Owen Bieber </a></li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="may95">May 1995</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><dl>
</dl>
<p><a href="bombing.htm"><b>The Oklahoma City Bombing</b> </a></p>
<dl>
<dd>We join all Americans in expressing shock, outrage and sorrow over the terrorist 
bombing of a federal building in Oklahoma City and the murder of 166 people. This 
tragedy will long be remembered as one of America's darkest moments.... </dd>
</dl>
</li>
<li><a href="cbasin.htm">Caribbean Basin Trade Security Act </a></li>
<li><a href="insuphwy.htm">The Information Superhighway </a></li>
<li><a href="intlaborg.htm">The International Labor Organization </a></li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="feb95">February 1995</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><dl>
</dl>
<p><a href="feb95/attack/attack.html"><b>The Attack on Working Families</b></a> </p>
<dl>
<dd>Anti-worker interests are using their control of Congress and numerous state houses 
to launch an assault on working American families ...</dd>
</dl>
</li>
<li><a href="trade.htm">Trade Deficit </a></li>
<li><a href="bribe.htm">Bribery in International Transactions </a></li>
<li><a href="peso.htm">The Peso Crisis </a></li>
<li><a href="davis.htm">Davis-Bacon </a></li>
<li><a href="service.htm">The Service Contract Act </a></li>
<li><a href="voting.htm">Thirtieth Anniversary of the Voting Rights Act </a></li>
<li><a href="295stale.htm">Struggles at Staley, Caterpillar and Bridgestone/Firestone </a></li>
<li><a href="295compun.htm">Company Unions </a></li>
<li><a href="ssecur.htm">Social Security </a></li>
<li><a href="redcro.htm">The American Red Cross </a></li>
<li><a href="basebl.htm">Support for Major Leage Baseball Players </a></li>
<li><a href="fedwor.htm">Support for Federal Workers </a></li>
<li><a href="immigrat.htm">Immigration and the American Dream </a></li>
<li><a href="borgwa.htm">Borg-Warner Security Services </a></li>
